Bournemouth is working on a deal to sign Nigeria winger, Bright Osayi-Samuel before the end of the current transfer window. According to The Sun, the Cherries are looking to sign the Fenerbahce wideman on loan with a buy option. Â£12 would be required to get the deal done according to the report. The 25-year-old spent all his career in England before moving to Turkish giants, Galatasaray in January 2021. Osayi-Samuel started his career at Blackpool before proceeding to Queens Park Rangers in 2017. He scored 13 goals and provided 13 assists in 115 appearances, before his switch to Istanbul. The player made his debut for the Super Eagles against Portugal last November.